annotationA: Glycogen [starch] synthase; Transfers the glycosyl residue from UDPG to the non- reducing end of alpha-1,4-glucan. In larval skeletal muscle, isoform B is required for the formation of autophagosomes during starvation and during cloroquine-induced vacuolar myopathy
annotationB: UGP, isoform A; UTP:glucose-1-phosphate uridylyltransferase activity. It is involved in the biological process described with: UDP-glucose metabolic process
